1
00:00:18,170 --> 00:00:19,440
THE VILLAGE BARBER

2
00:00:27,050 --> 00:00:28,950
THE VILLAGE BARBER

3
00:00:29,550 --> 00:00:30,620
<i>I need to get some rest.</i>

4
00:00:30,820 --> 00:00:32,390
<i>Yes, let's get some rest.</i>
<i>First, let's sit down.</i>

5
00:00:33,590 --> 00:00:36,660
THE PASSIONATE PART-TIMER
FINALLY GETS A MOMENT TO SIT

6
00:00:37,390 --> 00:00:38,860
My back hurts.

7
00:00:38,930 --> 00:00:41,830
THEY BEGIN TO GROAN IN PAIN AGAIN

8
00:00:42,260 --> 00:00:46,730
JI-HUI BROWSES EVERY CORNER

9
00:00:47,300 --> 00:00:49,500
Ji-hui, how old are you?

10
00:00:49,900 --> 00:00:51,240
I'm nine.

11
00:00:51,310 --> 00:00:53,110
- You're nine?
- You're ten now.

12
00:00:53,770 --> 00:00:54,910
You're ten now?

13
00:00:54,980 --> 00:00:56,240
A FATHERLY SMILE AT HEARING HER AGE

14
00:00:57,340 --> 00:00:58,880
- Is she the same age as your girl?
- Yes.

15
00:01:00,480 --> 00:01:01,580
How adorable.

16
00:01:01,650 --> 00:01:03,520
THE DAD WITH A DAUGHTER
LOOKS AT HER ENDEARINGLY

17
00:01:03,580 --> 00:01:05,690
Back when we were doing a shoot

18
00:01:06,190 --> 00:01:09,160
we once had a team dinner
or some occasion like that.

19
00:01:09,220 --> 00:01:12,190
But you had to leave early,
and I asked why.

20
00:01:12,460 --> 00:01:14,230
Then you said
you had to pick up your daughter

21
00:01:15,200 --> 00:01:16,560
because otherwise,
your wife would scold you.

22
00:01:16,630 --> 00:01:18,600
Yes. Wait.

23
00:01:19,630 --> 00:01:21,770
Wait, she doesn't scold me.

24
00:01:22,340 --> 00:01:23,940
Is your wife

25
00:01:24,870 --> 00:01:25,940
the tougher one?

26
00:01:26,010 --> 00:01:27,270
No, not at all.

27
00:01:27,340 --> 00:01:28,510
She's not tough at all.

28
00:01:28,940 --> 00:01:31,050
She's a very reasonable person.

29
00:01:32,710 --> 00:01:34,010
She's very reasonable

30
00:01:34,820 --> 00:01:36,920
and she's great.

31
00:01:37,820 --> 00:01:39,120
She teaches me many things

32
00:01:39,990 --> 00:01:42,120
through conversations.

33
00:01:45,060 --> 00:01:46,360
- What?
- Wait, a call.

34
00:01:46,430 --> 00:01:47,560
Would you like to pick it up?

35
00:01:49,730 --> 00:01:52,300
Hello, you have reached
The Village Barber.

36
00:01:52,730 --> 00:01:53,930
Yes, ma'am.

37
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:55,800
SWITCHING
INTO HIS CUSTOMER-SERVICE VOICE

38
00:01:55,870 --> 00:01:57,810
Yes, Ji-hui and Seon-hui are here.

39
00:01:58,270 --> 00:02:00,110
ALL EARS

40
00:02:00,170 --> 00:02:02,210
You would like them back home?

41
00:02:02,610 --> 00:02:05,750
- Right now?
- <i>If they are there, send them home.</i>

42
00:02:06,580 --> 00:02:08,850
Yes, ma'am.
I'll bring the girls back home.

43
00:02:08,920 --> 00:02:10,080
- No!
- No...

44
00:02:10,150 --> 00:02:11,650
- Bye.
- It's Grandma.

45
00:02:12,350 --> 00:02:14,620
Did she ask to bring
Ji-hui and Seon-hui home?

46
00:02:14,690 --> 00:02:16,590
Babies.

47
00:02:16,660 --> 00:02:18,230
- Yes?
- Your fun time is over.

48
00:02:18,290 --> 00:02:19,460
You have to go home.

49
00:02:19,530 --> 00:02:21,000
Da-in, keep doing your homework.

50
00:02:21,060 --> 00:02:23,130
Ji-hui and Seon-hui,
you're coming with me.

51
00:02:24,160 --> 00:02:26,430
- I'll tag along too. One second.
- Sure.

52
00:02:26,500 --> 00:02:28,570
- RAIN, should I put on my jacket?
- Huh?

53
00:02:28,640 --> 00:02:30,100
- Yes, let's do that. It's cold.
- It is.

54
00:02:30,770 --> 00:02:33,710
THE PROFESSIONAL OUTDOOR WORKER
PUTS HIS JACKET ON VOLUNTARILY

55
00:02:33,770 --> 00:02:34,940
We'll be back.

56
00:02:35,010 --> 00:02:37,380
THE QUADRICYCLE
THE PART-TIMER CAME ON

57
00:02:37,440 --> 00:02:38,850
- Girls, do you want to hop on?
- Yes.

58
00:02:38,910 --> 00:02:40,150
Should we take the quadricycle?

59
00:02:40,210 --> 00:02:43,150
- It's boring to walk home.
- It's a quadricycle!

60
00:02:43,220 --> 00:02:44,280
A quadricycle.

61
00:02:44,690 --> 00:02:46,450
- A quadricycle.
- Can you two pedal?

62
00:02:46,520 --> 00:02:48,060
- Yes.
- Yes, I'm good at riding bicycles.

63
00:02:48,120 --> 00:02:49,960
Let's go!
But I don't know where you live.

64
00:02:50,020 --> 00:02:51,530
- Tell us where.
- I know where.

65
00:02:51,590 --> 00:02:53,160
We'll tell you.

66
00:02:53,230 --> 00:02:54,600
It won't move.

67
00:02:54,660 --> 00:02:55,830
SPEEDING UP WITH HIS MUSCLES

68
00:02:55,900 --> 00:02:57,430
Have you two got money?

69
00:02:57,500 --> 00:02:59,030
- Yes.
- Really?

70
00:02:59,100 --> 00:03:00,400
This taxi ride will cost a lot.

71
00:03:01,100 --> 00:03:02,440
Left or right?

72
00:03:02,500 --> 00:03:03,770
This side!

73
00:03:03,840 --> 00:03:06,140
- We're going to Ms. Ou's place?
- Yes.

74
00:03:07,010 --> 00:03:08,640
- Ma'am!
- Grandma!

75
00:03:08,710 --> 00:03:10,010
Grandma!

76
00:03:10,880 --> 00:03:13,810
Goodness, those rascals
are having fun.

77
00:03:13,880 --> 00:03:15,480
They're having fun with the uncles.

78
00:03:15,550 --> 00:03:16,550
MS. OU CAME OUT TO MEET THE KIDS

79
00:03:18,490 --> 00:03:20,020
- You're here.
- Ms. Ou!

80
00:03:20,090 --> 00:03:21,520
Ms. Ou is right here.

81
00:03:21,590 --> 00:03:23,160
- It's been a while.
- Yes.

82
00:03:23,220 --> 00:03:24,730
- Hello, ma'am.
- Goodness.

83
00:03:24,790 --> 00:03:27,160
- He's a new part-timer.
- I'm a new member.

84
00:03:27,860 --> 00:03:29,900
- You may get off, Ji-hui.
- Grandma!

85
00:03:29,960 --> 00:03:31,730
- Goodness.
- Nice to meet you, ma'am.

86
00:03:32,370 --> 00:03:34,270
Sorry? Where are we going?

87
00:03:34,540 --> 00:03:36,900
ESCORTED INSIDE SMOOTHLY

88
00:03:36,970 --> 00:03:38,340
Hello.

89
00:03:38,410 --> 00:03:40,170
Ms. Ou.

90
00:03:40,240 --> 00:03:42,510
It's been pretty chilly
since yesterday. Aren't you cold?

91
00:03:42,580 --> 00:03:43,580
No.

92
00:03:44,880 --> 00:03:46,080
Are you giving up? Why?

93
00:03:46,680 --> 00:03:47,750
I'm tired.

94
00:03:49,450 --> 00:03:51,350
Wait. The purpose of my visit...

95
00:03:52,020 --> 00:03:53,350
I didn't come here to read a book.

96
00:03:53,420 --> 00:03:55,590
- What was the reason?
- I came to get a haircut.

97
00:03:56,090 --> 00:03:57,320
- Da-in?
- Yes.

98
00:03:57,390 --> 00:03:59,030
- You came for a haircut?
- Yes.

99
00:03:59,090 --> 00:04:00,130
For real?

100
00:04:01,230 --> 00:04:03,060
But I ended up doing my homework.

101
00:04:04,130 --> 00:04:05,770
UNTIL NOW, DA-IN

102
00:04:05,830 --> 00:04:08,200
PLAYED WITH THE UNCLES
IN THE RECEPTION ROOM

103
00:04:08,770 --> 00:04:10,670
Deliver these for us, please.

104
00:04:10,740 --> 00:04:13,440
SHE HAS BEEN HELPING OUT
AT THE BARBERSHOP

105
00:04:13,510 --> 00:04:15,340
Da-in and Seon-hui, do you want
your hair done, too?

106
00:04:15,410 --> 00:04:16,880
- What?
- Do you want your hair done?

107
00:04:17,380 --> 00:04:20,110
HESITANT

108
00:04:20,550 --> 00:04:23,280
DA-IN HAD BEEN OBSERVING

109
00:04:23,350 --> 00:04:26,290
BOSS PARK'S HAIRCUTTING SKILLS

110
00:04:27,220 --> 00:04:29,220
Miss, please take your seat.

111
00:04:29,290 --> 00:04:32,390
- Okay. One second.
- Yes, please take your time.

112
00:04:33,560 --> 00:04:34,560
DA-IN: CHILDREN'S HAIRCUT

113
00:04:34,630 --> 00:04:37,200
Princess Da-in,
are you ready to cut your hair?

114
00:04:38,600 --> 00:04:40,800
Should I cut off 5 cm?

115
00:04:40,870 --> 00:04:42,570
- Or 10 cm?
- Or 10 cm?

116
00:04:42,640 --> 00:04:44,040
Will you cut it into a bob?

117
00:04:44,100 --> 00:04:47,570
- I want it a bit longer than a bob.
- A bit longer?

118
00:04:47,940 --> 00:04:49,710
About 7 to 8cm?

119
00:04:49,780 --> 00:04:52,250
Okay, I get it. I'll see if I can...

120
00:04:53,880 --> 00:04:55,920
I get to cut your hair at last.

121
00:04:55,980 --> 00:04:58,350
- Finally. She's our VIP.
- I agree.

122
00:04:58,420 --> 00:05:02,460
- Da-in, do you have money to pay?
- I do.

123
00:05:03,090 --> 00:05:04,420
Put it on my tab.

124
00:05:04,490 --> 00:05:07,130
Okay. You don't need to pay, Da-in.

125
00:05:07,190 --> 00:05:10,000
- We won't take it.
- Thank you.

126
00:05:10,060 --> 00:05:11,600
The length right now...

127
00:05:11,830 --> 00:05:14,230
THINKING CAREFULLY

128
00:05:14,300 --> 00:05:16,470
HE'S BACK TO BEING
THE THOUGHTFUL BOSS PARK

129
00:05:16,540 --> 00:05:17,840
Look at the length right now.

130
00:05:18,140 --> 00:05:19,470
It's this long.

131
00:05:19,540 --> 00:05:20,540
SHOWING HER THE MIRROR

132
00:05:20,610 --> 00:05:22,240
If you cut this much off...

133
00:05:22,310 --> 00:05:23,310
CHECKING THE LENGTH SHE WANTS

134
00:05:23,380 --> 00:05:24,810
- About...
- It'll be this long.

135
00:05:24,880 --> 00:05:27,180
- Okay. That will do.
- Is that okay?

136
00:05:27,250 --> 00:05:30,050
- Like this.
- Da-in, you're a fifth grader.

137
00:05:30,120 --> 00:05:32,490
- What?
- Let's go for a big girl look.

138
00:05:32,550 --> 00:05:33,750
I was a big girl by fourth grade...

139
00:05:33,820 --> 00:05:35,260
They're back.

140
00:05:36,890 --> 00:05:38,690
- Welcome back.
- Hey.

141
00:05:39,190 --> 00:05:41,600
- I'll park here.
- No, please park over there.

142
00:05:41,660 --> 00:05:42,860
Okay.

143
00:05:43,360 --> 00:05:45,500
Jeez. Why is this so heavy?

144
00:05:45,570 --> 00:05:46,970
- Oh, my.
- Okay.

145
00:05:47,030 --> 00:05:49,100
Almost there. We're good now.

146
00:05:52,440 --> 00:05:54,070
- We have great news.
- What is it?

147
00:05:54,140 --> 00:05:56,280
- We got some corn.
- Wow, corn.

148
00:05:56,640 --> 00:05:58,950
EARNED CORN FOR HELPING OUT
WHILE THEY WERE THERE

149
00:05:59,010 --> 00:06:01,110
- We got paid for our labor.
- Good work.

150
00:06:01,750 --> 00:06:04,320
- I noticed something odd, BO GUM.
- Yes?

151
00:06:04,380 --> 00:06:06,650
I've been here for five hours,
but it feels like five days.

152
00:06:07,120 --> 00:06:08,520
THE VILLAGE BARBER
WHERE TIME FLIES

153
00:06:08,590 --> 00:06:11,160
- It's fascinating.
- We'll be done in an hour.

154
00:06:11,230 --> 00:06:12,330
Yes, it's so weird.

155
00:06:13,890 --> 00:06:15,260
I'm exhausted.

156
00:06:15,330 --> 00:06:17,330
He feels like
he's been here for five days.

157
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:19,600
I keep craving something sweet.

158
00:06:21,800 --> 00:06:25,610
THE EXHAUSTED PART-TIMER
PICKED UP SOME SNACKS

159
00:06:26,240 --> 00:06:29,980
CORN PUFFS

160
00:06:30,710 --> 00:06:31,750
GROAN

161
00:06:32,850 --> 00:06:34,180
HE SWORE HE WOULDN'T SNACK

162
00:06:34,250 --> 00:06:37,720
BUT HE CHOMPS OUT OF THE BAG

163
00:06:38,150 --> 00:06:39,720
At this point

164
00:06:40,250 --> 00:06:41,960
I start to feel anxious
when the phone rings

165
00:06:42,020 --> 00:06:43,320
or when someone walks in.

166
00:06:43,390 --> 00:06:45,060
- It's alarming.
- Yes.

167
00:06:45,130 --> 00:06:46,590
- I think, "What could it be?"
- it's sudden.

168
00:06:46,790 --> 00:06:48,000
You think, "Is something going on?"

169
00:06:48,060 --> 00:06:50,400
HAGGARD

170
00:06:51,570 --> 00:06:53,800
BUSY SNACKING

171
00:06:53,870 --> 00:06:55,070
SNIFFLE

172
00:06:58,410 --> 00:07:02,540
PART-TIMER'S STATE OF MIND:
AWAY FOR A MOMENT

173
00:07:04,380 --> 00:07:07,380
I'll cut it right off for you.

174
00:07:07,680 --> 00:07:09,280
BUT WAIT, A HAIR CLIPPER?

175
00:07:09,350 --> 00:07:10,620
- A hair clipper?
- A hair clipper...

176
00:07:11,550 --> 00:07:12,790
I'll use a hair clipper.

177
00:07:12,850 --> 00:07:15,190
WHY DID HE PICK UP
A HAIR CLIPPER FOR A WOMEN'S CUT?

178
00:07:15,890 --> 00:07:17,890
FOR BOBBED HAIR

179
00:07:17,960 --> 00:07:20,490
THE FIRST TOOL YOU NEED IN TRIMMING

180
00:07:20,560 --> 00:07:22,700
A HAIR CLIPPER

181
00:07:23,060 --> 00:07:25,870
REASON:
IT CREATES THE 1ST GUIDELINE

182
00:07:25,930 --> 00:07:29,140
BEFORE USING SCISSORS
TO TRIM AND ADD DETAILS

183
00:07:29,700 --> 00:07:33,170
- It's kind of scary.
- No, you'll be fine with me.

184
00:07:33,240 --> 00:07:34,610
Don't be scared.

185
00:07:34,680 --> 00:07:37,910
I've never had my hair cut
with a hair clipper before.

186
00:07:37,980 --> 00:07:39,580
- No, right?
- I've only used scissors.

187
00:07:41,080 --> 00:07:42,780
HE REASSURES HER

188
00:07:42,850 --> 00:07:47,090
AND BRAVELY BEGINS
TO CUT WITH A HAIR CLIPPER

189
00:07:47,750 --> 00:07:50,020
WILL BO GUM

190
00:07:50,090 --> 00:07:52,890
BE ABLE TO CUT HER HAIR
WITH A HAIR CLIPPER SUCCESSFULLY?

191
00:07:52,960 --> 00:07:56,330
TREMBLING WITH NERVES

192
00:07:57,500 --> 00:08:03,100
NERVOUS

193
00:08:07,010 --> 00:08:09,510
THE CUT BEGINS

194
00:08:12,180 --> 00:08:14,250
CAUTIOUS

195
00:08:15,180 --> 00:08:19,950
MAKING SURE THE LINE STAYS STEADY

196
00:08:20,020 --> 00:08:25,860
AS HE CUTS A HANDFUL AT A TIME

197
00:08:26,590 --> 00:08:28,530
VERY NEAT

198
00:08:29,100 --> 00:08:31,370
BOSS PARK CHECKS ON DA-IN
AS SOON AS HE'S DONE

199
00:08:31,430 --> 00:08:33,970
- Isn't it cool?
- It's kind of scary.

200
00:08:34,400 --> 00:08:38,010
- It's nothing to be scared of.
- I've never cut my hair with this.

201
00:08:38,070 --> 00:08:39,440
- Am I the first?
- Yes.

202
00:08:39,710 --> 00:08:42,140
Only my mom
had cut my hair to this day.

203
00:08:42,840 --> 00:08:44,210
- Really?
- My mom.

204
00:08:44,280 --> 00:08:46,250
I've never been
to a salon in my life.

205
00:08:46,310 --> 00:08:49,020
- Never?
- My mom always cut my hair for me.

206
00:08:49,450 --> 00:08:51,320
Oh, really?

207
00:08:51,390 --> 00:08:53,190
HER FIRST TIME
LETTING SOMEONE ELSE CUT HER HAIR

208
00:08:53,250 --> 00:08:55,020
GRABBING

209
00:08:55,520 --> 00:08:56,990
LOOK

210
00:08:57,060 --> 00:08:58,930
- I cut off this much right now.
- Really?

211
00:08:58,990 --> 00:09:01,090
UNCLE BO GUM SHOWS HER EVERYTHING
TO EASE HER FIRST EXPERIENCE

212
00:09:01,160 --> 00:09:03,200
You cut off a lot, Da-in.

213
00:09:03,260 --> 00:09:04,900
Will you look to your right?

214
00:09:05,700 --> 00:09:08,000
STARTING WITH THE 1ST CUT ON THE SIDE

215
00:09:08,070 --> 00:09:09,700
NERVOUS AND FROZEN

216
00:09:09,770 --> 00:09:11,100
Yes, keep looking that way.

217
00:09:14,140 --> 00:09:16,680
MATCHING THE LENGTH IN THE BACK

218
00:09:16,740 --> 00:09:20,980
AND CUTTING WITHOUT HESITATION

219
00:09:21,310 --> 00:09:22,750
Now, can you look to your left?

220
00:09:23,150 --> 00:09:24,250
Thanks.

221
00:09:25,450 --> 00:09:27,720
DOES NOT HESITATE

222
00:09:27,790 --> 00:09:30,660
TO CHOP OFF

223
00:09:30,720 --> 00:09:33,830
SHE ALREADY LOOKS QUITE DIFFERENT
AFTER THE 1ST CUT

224
00:09:33,890 --> 00:09:36,900
Why do I feel like
I've turned into my sister?

225
00:09:36,960 --> 00:09:38,200
I look like my sister.

226
00:09:38,270 --> 00:09:39,870
- Do you not like it?
- It's not that.

227
00:09:39,930 --> 00:09:41,970
No, it's just the same length
as my sister's.

228
00:09:42,600 --> 00:09:44,340
But it looks good on you.

229
00:09:45,410 --> 00:09:47,670
It goes so well
with your smart image.

230
00:09:49,340 --> 00:09:52,380
NEXT, SECTIONING THE HAIR
TO START WORKING WITH SCISSORS

231
00:09:52,450 --> 00:09:55,820
ROLLING UP ONE HANDFUL EACH

232
00:09:56,850 --> 00:09:59,120
PARTING INTO DIFFERENT SECTIONS

233
00:09:59,190 --> 00:10:01,960
What do you think
about this style with the hairpins?

234
00:10:02,690 --> 00:10:03,890
This style?

235
00:10:03,960 --> 00:10:04,990
DONG-YEON'S JOKE RELAXES HER

236
00:10:07,530 --> 00:10:08,530
What is that?

237
00:10:08,600 --> 00:10:10,530
Do you want to see something magical?

238
00:10:10,600 --> 00:10:13,900
- Sure.
- Now, what is this?

239
00:10:13,970 --> 00:10:15,840
- A tissue paper.
- It's a tissue paper.

240
00:10:15,900 --> 00:10:18,140
- Yes.
- I will

241
00:10:18,870 --> 00:10:20,040
use this tissue paper

242
00:10:20,540 --> 00:10:22,510
to turn it into a tissue paper snail.

243
00:10:22,580 --> 00:10:24,280
- A snail?
- Look.

244
00:10:24,340 --> 00:10:25,510
TRYING NOT TO LAUGH

245
00:10:25,950 --> 00:10:27,250
I've never seen this, either.

246
00:10:27,310 --> 00:10:29,020
A TISSUE SNAIL TRICK
FROM AN UNINVITED MAGICIAN

247
00:10:29,080 --> 00:10:31,380
- But Da-in probably won't...
- She won't be fooled.

248
00:10:31,450 --> 00:10:33,520
Her cognitive ability
is much higher than most adults.

249
00:10:33,590 --> 00:10:35,790
- She's smart.
- You'll make a snail?

250
00:10:35,860 --> 00:10:37,720
I'll make a snail model.

251
