1981
01:31:16,730 --> 01:31:19,260
- Today I prepared
- Yes.

1982
01:31:19,700 --> 01:31:22,200
a <i>gukbap </i>with pork neck

1983
01:31:22,260 --> 01:31:24,270
- and shoulder meat.
- I see.

1984
01:31:24,770 --> 01:31:26,400
Who cut the kelp today?

1985
01:31:27,000 --> 01:31:29,810
CHEF KWAK'S SCOLDING
TURNS THE AIR FRIGID

1986
01:31:30,240 --> 01:31:31,540
Was this radish
harvested in the fall?

1987
01:31:32,310 --> 01:31:35,010
They're not all the same thickness.

1988
01:31:35,080 --> 01:31:36,450
- Yes, chef.
- Be more careful.

1989
01:31:36,510 --> 01:31:39,510
Chef Kwak. Table four says
their food is overcooked.

1990
01:31:41,080 --> 01:31:42,720
If they don't want to eat,
they can leave.

1991
01:31:43,890 --> 01:31:44,920
WHAT A WEIRD RESTAURANT

1992
01:31:44,990 --> 01:31:46,360
This is insane.

1993
01:31:47,520 --> 01:31:48,890
Did you hear the sigh?

1994
01:31:49,420 --> 01:31:50,960
"If they don't want to eat,
they can leave."

1995
01:31:53,700 --> 01:31:54,960
It's too funny to keep going.

1996
01:31:55,030 --> 01:31:57,600
- It's hard. He's too good.
- It's hard to keep a poker face.

1997
01:31:57,670 --> 01:31:59,300
I'm out because I laughed.

1998
01:32:00,100 --> 01:32:01,670
Thank you so much for the food.

1999
01:32:01,740 --> 01:32:03,540
Think of it as an invigorating tonic.

2000
01:32:03,970 --> 01:32:06,910
- Thank you for the food.
- Thank you.

2001
01:32:07,540 --> 01:32:09,410
- Enjoy.
- You need to taste it.

2002
01:32:11,380 --> 01:32:12,580
It's incredible.

2003
01:32:12,650 --> 01:32:14,880
IN AWE

2004
01:32:15,950 --> 01:32:17,320
- Gosh.
- Eat it with this.

2005
01:32:18,350 --> 01:32:20,660
I stif-fried it
with fish sauce and cabbage.

2006
01:32:21,220 --> 01:32:23,290
The cabbage goes all the way down.

2007
01:32:25,160 --> 01:32:26,360
It's really good.

2008
01:32:27,660 --> 01:32:29,330
It's nice to see you enjoy it.

2009
01:32:29,400 --> 01:32:30,670
THIS IS WHAT HE CAME TO SEE

2010
01:32:31,500 --> 01:32:34,940
IT WAS THEIR DAY OFF
AND IT WAS UNINTENTIONALLY DRAINING

2011
01:32:35,000 --> 01:32:37,810
NAM-NO CHEERED THEM UP

2012
01:32:39,340 --> 01:32:40,940
THE FROWN OF TRUTH

2013
01:32:42,040 --> 01:32:43,250
Are you okay?

2014
01:32:43,310 --> 01:32:46,520
THE CHICKEN TASTES INCREDIBLE

2015
01:32:46,580 --> 01:32:47,920
It's so tasty.

2016
01:32:49,650 --> 01:32:51,490
It feels a bit weird.

2017
01:32:52,220 --> 01:32:53,460
I'm in the countryside

2018
01:32:54,160 --> 01:32:55,760
eating with people
I never could've met.

2019
01:32:56,530 --> 01:32:57,890
It was worth the work.

2020
01:33:00,600 --> 01:33:01,860
I feel happy.

2021
01:33:01,930 --> 01:33:03,770
To think that food
can make you happy.

2022
01:33:05,700 --> 01:33:08,940
Being able to create
good memories for someone

2023
01:33:09,000 --> 01:33:10,370
makes you pretty happy.

2024
01:33:10,870 --> 01:33:11,940
Something like that.

2025
01:33:13,040 --> 01:33:15,040
I think it's the same for everyone.

2026
01:33:15,810 --> 01:33:18,250
We paint nails
and cut hair for people

2027
01:33:18,310 --> 01:33:21,120
and hear about their lives
as we do so.

2028
01:33:21,420 --> 01:33:23,620
They must all have fond memories.

2029
01:33:24,750 --> 01:33:26,790
You're more than halfway through.

2030
01:33:26,860 --> 01:33:28,160
- It must be a bit sad.
- It's sad.

2031
01:33:28,590 --> 01:33:29,590
One day...

2032
01:33:29,930 --> 01:33:32,430
It was over the weekend.

2033
01:33:32,490 --> 01:33:34,260
We had a fish-shaped bun day

2034
01:33:34,760 --> 01:33:36,600
and 30 to 40 people came by.

2035
01:33:36,670 --> 01:33:38,170
- It was crazy.
- Really?

2036
01:33:38,230 --> 01:33:40,800
- The whole village came, then.
- Almost everyone.

2037
01:33:40,870 --> 01:33:43,000
Everyone's so kind and generous.

2038
01:33:43,670 --> 01:33:46,540
They looked out for us.

2039
01:33:47,310 --> 01:33:52,750
The kids we played with
who we sent home before coming in.

2040
01:33:52,810 --> 01:33:56,380
They're both girls
who start fifth grade in March.

2041
01:33:56,950 --> 01:33:58,020
One made us...

2042
01:33:58,090 --> 01:33:59,520
I'm not wearing mine
in case I lose it.

2043
01:33:59,590 --> 01:34:00,720
Are you wearing yours?

2044
01:34:01,060 --> 01:34:03,690
She made bracelets for each of us.

2045
01:34:03,760 --> 01:34:04,890
- Is this it?
- Yes.

2046
01:34:05,560 --> 01:34:06,800
- There are two.
- I love it.

2047
01:34:07,860 --> 01:34:11,170
It looks luxurious. It's well-made.
She made it herself?

2048
01:34:12,330 --> 01:34:14,070
I'm starting to feel sad.

2049
01:34:14,770 --> 01:34:18,170
I've grown attached to everyone.

2050
01:34:18,970 --> 01:34:20,140
Actually

2051
01:34:20,610 --> 01:34:24,180
it's a short period and we see them
only a few hours a day.

2052
01:34:24,610 --> 01:34:26,980
- That's right.
- We just met strangers

2053
01:34:27,050 --> 01:34:29,480
whom we had no connections at all.

2054
01:34:30,020 --> 01:34:32,420
But they opened their hearts
to let us in

2055
01:34:33,520 --> 01:34:35,420
and treated us with warmth.

2056
01:34:36,790 --> 01:34:38,830
THEY MISSED THE RESIDENTS
DURING THEIR BRIEF BREAK

2057
01:34:38,890 --> 01:34:41,700
I think I'll miss Ms. Ra a lot, too.

2058
01:34:41,760 --> 01:34:43,430
It's hard to say goodbye.

2059
01:34:44,670 --> 01:34:46,100
Why are you tearing up?

2060
01:34:46,600 --> 01:34:48,240
He's crying. I see tears.

2061
01:34:52,540 --> 01:34:54,040
The thing is

2062
01:34:55,310 --> 01:34:57,980
I act cheeky and friendly
as if I'm approachable.

2063
01:34:59,480 --> 01:35:02,780
I find it a bit hard
to befriend people and open up.

2064
01:35:02,850 --> 01:35:04,550
Although on the outside

2065
01:35:05,150 --> 01:35:07,160
I look like
I have no problem with it.

2066
01:35:07,760 --> 01:35:12,830
That's because
I know what it's like to part ways.

2067
01:35:13,630 --> 01:35:14,900
It's a bit

2068
01:35:15,930 --> 01:35:17,800
upsetting.

2069
01:35:17,870 --> 01:35:20,070
So I always tried to keep a boundary.

2070
01:35:20,840 --> 01:35:24,740
I think I crossed that boundary
in the few days I was here

2071
01:35:24,810 --> 01:35:26,270
unconsciously.

2072
01:35:27,340 --> 01:35:29,980
<i>That's why I feel weird right now.</i>

2073
01:35:33,550 --> 01:35:35,450
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

2074
01:35:35,520 --> 01:35:37,190
- Happy New Year.
- Get back safely.

2075
01:35:37,250 --> 01:35:38,750
- Bye.
- Take care.

2076
01:35:38,820 --> 01:35:39,890
SENDING THE FAIRY GODMOTHER
YOON NAM-NO OFF

2077
01:35:40,360 --> 01:35:41,760
- Goodbye.
- Bye!

2078
01:35:45,690 --> 01:35:48,230
LATE THAT NIGHT

2079
01:35:49,560 --> 01:35:52,730
THE BARBERSHOP'S STILL OPEN

2080
01:35:53,670 --> 01:35:56,400
SNIPPING SOUNDS

2081
01:35:57,270 --> 01:36:00,140
BO GUM ASKED SOME CREW MEMBERS
TO VOLUNTEER FOR PRACTICE CUTS

2082
01:36:01,240 --> 01:36:04,580
EVEN ON HIS DAY OFF

2083
01:36:05,450 --> 01:36:09,990
BO GUM PRACTICES
FOR THE CLIENTS HE'LL MEET TOMORROW

2084
01:36:10,050 --> 01:36:13,760
<i>I went to Mount Deogyusan</i>
<i>and the downtown area</i>

2085
01:36:13,820 --> 01:36:19,130
<i>and that gave me something else</i>
<i>to talk about with the locals.</i>

2086
01:36:19,190 --> 01:36:21,800
I'm looking forward
to see who will come by tomorrow.

2087
01:36:22,800 --> 01:36:25,570
Even if more people come over

2088
01:36:26,000 --> 01:36:28,440
I have the confidence
that I think I can manage.

2089
01:36:29,800 --> 01:36:31,770
<i>I look forward to tomorrow.</i>

2090
01:36:37,180 --> 01:36:38,280
<i>We're open for business.</i>

2091
01:36:38,710 --> 01:36:39,880
<i>- It's going to be hectic.</i>
<i>- Yeah.</i>

2092
01:36:39,950 --> 01:36:41,120
BACK TO BUSINESS
THE VILLAGE BARBER IS BUSY

2093
01:36:41,180 --> 01:36:42,180
Pull yourself together.

2094
01:36:42,250 --> 01:36:43,720
<i>Just one day off feels</i>
<i>like we're back after ages.</i>

2095
01:36:43,790 --> 01:36:44,990
<i>It's a time bomb.</i>

2096
01:36:45,050 --> 01:36:47,390
<i>Things aren't going so well today.</i>

2097
01:36:47,460 --> 01:36:49,960
<i>I'm so clumsy and careless.</i>

2098
01:36:50,030 --> 01:36:51,760
<i>- Are they brothers?</i>
<i>- Three brothers.</i>

2099
01:36:52,360 --> 01:36:53,730
<i>- Should we do a cheer?</i>
<i>- Oh, wow.</i>

2100
01:36:53,800 --> 01:36:54,900
LET'S START OVER!

2101
01:36:54,960 --> 01:36:57,030
As long as it's not too short.

2102
01:36:57,100 --> 01:36:58,600
<i>I'll cut your hair now.</i>

2103
01:36:59,100 --> 01:37:00,540
I cut it too short.

2104
01:37:00,940 --> 01:37:02,070
I'm sorry.

2105
01:37:03,240 --> 01:37:04,840
I think something went in my eye.

2106
01:37:04,910 --> 01:37:06,810
Maybe about this short for the bangs.

2107
01:37:07,140 --> 01:37:08,480
Okay.

2108
01:37:08,540 --> 01:37:10,150
18-MONTH-OLD
THE YOUNGEST CUSTOMER EVER

2109
01:37:10,210 --> 01:37:11,480
<i>Sit right here.</i>

2110
01:37:11,550 --> 01:37:13,150
Oh, you don't like it?

2111
01:37:13,210 --> 01:37:14,250
You don't like it.

2112
01:37:14,320 --> 01:37:15,850
<i>I'll start cutting your hair now.</i>

2113
01:37:16,380 --> 01:37:19,990
<i>- Baby bear is so cute</i>
<i>- Baby bear is so cute</i>

2114
01:37:20,060 --> 01:37:22,960
<i>- Job well done</i>
<i>- Job well done</i>

2115
01:37:23,490 --> 01:37:24,560
- Hello.
- Hello.

2116
01:37:24,630 --> 01:37:27,000
HIGH SCHOOL GIRLS SHOW UP
AT THE VILLAGE BARBER

2117
01:37:27,060 --> 01:37:28,930
I want to make a donation.

2118
01:37:29,000 --> 01:37:30,200
<i>She's donating her hair.</i>

2119
01:37:30,270 --> 01:37:31,370
That's amazing.

2120
01:37:31,430 --> 01:37:32,800
<i>I'll do the best I can.</i>

2121
01:37:32,870 --> 01:37:36,040
HOW WILL THEIR ROLLERCOASTER RIDE
OF A BUSINESS UNFOLD?

2122
01:37:40,280 --> 01:37:41,540
THE VILLAGE BARBER

2123
01:37:49,180 --> 01:37:51,050
THE VILLAGE BARBER

2124
01:37:53,050 --> 01:37:55,060
Subtitles by Eunsook Youn,
Hoyoung Yun, and Jennifer Lim
